      "content": "i see. so the main trial failed to show efficacy, and we're basically pivoting to a much smaller niche based on a subgroup analysis. if i tell the board we're \"on track\" or \"seeing great results\" when the primary endpoint was a failure, they're going to grill me on why we aren't declaring the trial unsuccessful. how should i frame the failure of the primary endpoint so it doesn't kill the funding? i don't want them to think the drug is a dud.",
